1 Sec. 6. 5 MRSA §4583, as amended by PL 2021, c. 366, §11, is further amended to
2 read:
3 §4583. Application
4 Nothing in this This Act may not be construed to prohibit or limit the exercise of the
5 privilege of every person and the agent of any person having the right to sell, rent, lease or
6 manage a housing accommodation to set up and enforce specifications in the selling,
7 renting, leasing or letting or in the furnishings of facilities or services in connection with
8 the facilities that are consistent with business necessity and are not based on the race, color,
9 sex, sexual orientation or gender identity, physical or mental disability, religion, country of
10 ancestral origin or, familial status, military status, source of income or veteran status of or
11 the receipt of public assistance payments by any prospective or actual purchaser, lessee,
12 tenant or occupant. Nothing in this This Act may not be construed to prohibit or limit the
13 exercise of the privilege of every person and the agent of any person making loans for or
14 offering financial assistance in the acquisition, construction, rehabilitation, repair or
15 maintenance of housing accommodations to set standards and preferences, terms,
16 conditions, limitations or specifications for the granting of loans or financial assistance that
17 are consistent with business necessity and are not based on the race, color, sex, sexual
18 orientation or gender identity, physical or mental disability, religion, country of ancestral
19 origin or, familial status, military status, source of income or veteran status of or the receipt
20 of public assistance payments by the applicant for a loan or financial assistance or of any
21 existing or prospective owner, lessee, tenant or occupant of a housing accommodation. This
22 Act may not be construed to prohibit any person from providing or otherwise making
23 available any services or other assistance to individuals receiving federal, state or local
24 housing assistance.
25 SUMMARY
2266 This bill amends the Maine Human Rights Act to prohibit housing discrimination on
2277 the basis of an individual's military status, veteran status or source of income. The bill
2288 defines "source of income" to include income from any federal, state or local public
2299 assistance program, including payments under the United States Social Security Act,
3300 medical assistance and housing vouchers; income received by court order; any payment
3311 from a trust, guardian, conservator, cosigner or relative; and any other lawful source of
3322 income or funds.
